    ğŸ”¹ `--static-output` --> ğŸ”’ Generates static C code. Meaning it does not use global variables.
    ğŸ”¹ `--header` --> ğŸ“ Only creates the header file `.h`.
    ğŸ”¹ `--c` --> ğŸ“„ Only creates the code file `.c`.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ gdk-pixbuf-csource image.png > image.h

    ğŸ”¹ Generates C code for image.png and saves it in image.h.

    $ gdk-pixbuf-csource --raw-inline --name=image_data image.jpg image.c

    ğŸ”¹ Converts the image image.jpg to C code, embeds it as raw data, names the array image_data, and saves it in image.c.

